item.title: I need help looking for music like this
item.dc:creator: Fnork
item.description:
If I might sneak into this thread with my own request for help (apologies, Fong), but I’m looking for if there’s a specific genre of music where it’s orchestral with a strong vocal accompaniment (usually in Latin), usually dark and foreboding sounding.

If you want something more genuine you should try Mozart’s Requiem.

It’s 56 minutes long and goes in movements, so there’s a lot of variation if you want several distinct pieces.

item.title: I need help looking for music like this
item.dc:creator: _rot_fodder
item.description:
danielsangeo:

If I might sneak into this thread with my own request for help (apologies, Fong), but I’m looking for if there’s a specific genre of music where it’s orchestral with a strong vocal accompaniment (usually in Latin), usually dark and foreboding sounding.

Well, I think these qualifies, even if they aren’t quite up to today’s standards quality-wise.

Warlock - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5vqN9zNAxr4&feature=relmfu

Barbarian - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2V0jHblkspo&feature=relmfu

Necromancer - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0g-qVAZ01Dw

I especially like Barbarian tonight, but my favorites switch around depending on my mood. I would love to hear them remastered one day.

item.title: I need help looking for music like this
item.dc:creator: Eric_Fong
item.description:
danielsangeo:

If I might sneak into this thread with my own request for help (apologies, Fong), but I’m looking for if there’s a specific genre of music where it’s orchestral with a strong vocal accompaniment (usually in Latin), usually dark and foreboding sounding.

Examples of the type of the music that I’m referring to would be:
Duel of the Fates from Star Wars, Consumite Furore from Phantasmagoria, Carl Orff’s O Fortuna from Carmina Burana, and One Winged Angel from Final Fantasy VII. I love that kind of thing and want find more of it. Is it a specific genre or what?

Thanks!

It’s okay, I got what I need anyway.

Something like orchester + latin lyric I guess. I remember a good song from a flash game called “Undead Chase”

https://www.newgrounds.com/audio/listen/368924 (Lyric begin after 1 minute)
